    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-09T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="427"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857/239</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-09T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3651. Department advised that British steamer <hi rend="italic">Trevarrick</hi>
                        [<hi rend="italic">Trevarrack</hi>], with American citizens on board, was
                    sunk by German <pb facs="0608" n="322" xml:id="pg_322"/> submarine 90 miles off
                    Ouessant [Ushant] Point, November 16, and that ship was carrying cargo of grain
                    from Buenos Aires to Hull.</p>
                <p>Request of Foreign Minister prompt investigation and report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
